                <c level="subseries">
                    <did><unittitle>Subseries 2: Musical Scores, <unitdate type="inclusive">1925-1978</unitdate>
                        </unittitle>
                    </did>
                    <scopecontent><p>A collection of original scores and arrangements from the entire length of Serly’s career. The works include ballets, songs, chamber music, symphonies,
                    
                        and experimental music, all in different states of completion: parts, conductor scores, revisions, sketches, microfilms, and transparencies. Several pieces also demonstrate Serly’s expertise as an arranger, with works by Bartók, Bach, Schubert, and his father, Lajos Serly.</p>
                    </scopecontent>
